  "A logistic model because the distance eventually levels off at a maximum carrying capacity": "",
  "An exponential model because the distance doubles with each successive time interval measured": "",
  "A linear log-log plot with slope 2 implies y ∝ x², consistent with the physics equation d = ½gt².": "",
  "A pharmaceutical company tracks the concentration of a drug in the bloodstream over 24 hours. The data curves downward at a decreasing rate. A linear model gives r² = 0.72 with a curved residual plot; an exponential decay model gives r² = 0.96 with random residuals. Which model should be used?": "",
